Information: This is a list of vehicles and DNA from a starting population that outperformed every other population I ran. They maintained a constant population of ~160 members for 30 minutes. There was a consistent amount of green, young, healthy Vehicles and red, old, unhealthy ones. The population continued to maintain this gradation. No vehicle lived for a disproportionate amount of time. All lived for a similar amount of time and mostly reproduced before dying. This lists 5 vehicles in their entirety and the environmental conditions along with them. The chance to spawn food or posion is simply a percent (random(1) < foodSpawnChance). For reproduction the chance to reproduce was calculated as (1 / (population * reproductionChance)) for every encounter. The likelyhood that a Vehicle seeks a mate, however is determined by DNA. The reproduction chance is active any time two vehicles are near each other regardless if they sought a vehicle to reproduce with. This configuration created a stable population that very closley mimicked a population of animals that was stable for minutes on end with no sign of changing. After the 5 vehicles is a list of 300 DNAs from random Vehicles. The first 100 are from one point (around 45000 dead) and the next 100 are from another point (around 60000 dead) the last 100 are from another point (around 192000 dead)
